abecc072641cae339528bec58d564f63.summary: Nepal's Prime Minister K.P. Sharma Oli resigned after widespread protests sparked by a social media ban and allegations of government corruption. The demonstrations, largely driven by the country's youth, continued even after the ban was lifted, leading to violent clashes that resulted in at least 19 deaths. The unrest, one of the worst in decades, also saw the federal parliament and the homes of several politicians set on fire. Oli's resignation came in the wake of his cabinet members quitting and no immediate solution to the crisis.
